    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The Solidity optimizer currently does not have a concept of lifetime of memory objects. Because of that, the `bytes` created in `abi.encodeWithSelector(Z.test.selector)` is persistently allocated while in `atest.test();` is it allocated only temporarily.\r\n\r\nI'm closing this since we are very aware of this optimization opportunity.",
